1. The Oxidation/Reduction Trap\
\
 *********WARNING**************\
Don't blend these two incredibly powerful, opposing chemical forces: Chlorine Dioxide (\\(ClO_\{2\}\\)), which is a severe oxidant, and Methylene Blue, which is a powerful reducing agent (an electron donor). [1, 2("https://taylormedicalgroup.net/holistic-cosmetic-services-atlanta-ga/iv-therapy-atlanta-georgia/methylene-blue-iv-atlanta/")]\
\
\
  [WHAT WILL HAPPEN IN THE BOTTLE ]\
  Chlorine Dioxide (Oxidant)  <===(Chemical War)===>  Methylene Blue (Reducer)\
                                        \uc0\u9474 \
                                        
\f1 \uc0\u9660 
\f0 \
  * Chemicals completely neutralize each other\
  * Bleaches the Methylene Blue into a clear, inactive state (Leucomethylene Blue)\
  * Destroys your skin's raw topical defense shield\
\
    \'95    The Neutralization War: When you mix \\(ClO_\{2\}\\) and Methylene Blue in the same liquid, they immediately attack each other. The Chlorine Dioxide aggressively strips electrons away from the Methylene Blue molecule.\
\
    \'95    The Structural Result: This reaction completely neutralizes both compounds. The \\(ClO_\{2\}\\) gets destroyed, and the Methylene Blue gets chemically bleached into an altered state called Leucomethylene Blue. While Leucomethylene Blue has some properties inside the mitochondria, the destructive reaction in the bottle means you are losing a massive amount of the raw, active potency of both your oxidant (\\(ClO_\{2\}\\)) and your reducer (MB) before they even cross your skin barrier. [1, 2("https://www.instagram.com/reel/DIJriJXJ-Zu/")]\
    \
    \'95    The DMSO Amplification Danger: Because DMSO alters your cell membranes to drive everything deep into your bloodstream, it is currently carrying those unstable, degraded chemical byproducts straight through your skin [1.5]. This is highly likely the exact cause of any localized skin irritation or redness you might feel.\
